All Implemented Interfaces:
Attribute, CatalogObject, CatalogObject.AccessControlled<CatalogObject.Grant.OnAttribute>, CatalogObject.Addressed<RegClass>, CatalogObject.Component, CatalogObject.Named<Lexicals.Identifier.Simple>, CatalogObjectImpl.AccessControlled<CatalogObject.Grant.OnAttribute>, CatalogObjectImpl.Named<Lexicals.Identifier.Simple>, CatalogObjectImpl.Nonshared<RegClass>
Enclosing class:
AttributeImpl
static class AttributeImpl.Cataloged extends AttributeImpl
An attribute that belongs to a full-fledged cataloged composite type.

It holds a reference to the relation that defines the composite type layout. While that can always be found from the class and object IDs of the object address, that is too much fuss for as often as relation() is called.
